Introduction to Python Project : FoodHub Data Analysis

Problem Statement

Foodhub is online food aggregator company. To improve its business they have hired a data scientist to extract information from the data which they have accumulated.

They want to get an idea on the demand of different restaurants which will hep them to improve customer experience.

Data Dictionary

order_id - Unique Id of the order

customer_id - ID of the customer who ordered the food

restaurant_name - Name of the restaurant

cuisine_type - Cusine ordered by the customer

cost_of_the_order - Cost of the order

day_of_the_week - Indicates whether the order is placed on weekday or weekend (Weekday is Monday to Friday and Weekend is Saturday and Sunday)

rating - Rating given by the customer out of 5.

food_preparation_time - Time in minutes taken by restaurant to prepare the food

delivery_time - Time(in minutes) taken by delivery person to deliver the food package

Question 13: The company wants to provide a promotional offer in the advertisement of the restaurants. The condition to get the offer is that the restaurants must have a rating count of more than 50 and the average rating should be greater than 4. Find the restaurants fulfilling the criteria to get the promotional offer. [3 marks]

In[221]:
filtered_df = df[df['rating'] != 'Not given']
filtered_df['rating'] = filtered_df['rating'].astype(float)

rating_counts = filtered_df.groupby('restaurant_name')['rating'].count()
qualified_restaurants_count = rating_counts[rating_counts > 50].index

mean_rating = filtered_df.groupby('restaurant_name')['rating'].mean()
qualified_restaurants_mean = mean_rating[mean_rating > 4].index

final_filtered_df = filtered_df[(filtered_df['restaurant_name'].isin(qualified_restaurants_count)) & (filtered_df['restaurant_name'].isin(qualified_restaurants_mean))]

Question 14: The company charges the restaurant 25% on the orders having cost greater than 20 dollars and 15% on the orders having cost greater than 5 dollars. Find the net revenue generated by the company across all orders. [3 marks]

In[224]:
# Write the code here
df_with_revenue25percent = df[df['cost_of_the_order'] > 20]
revenue25percent_order_sum = df_with_revenue25percent['cost_of_the_order'].sum()
total_25percentrevenue = 0.25 * revenue25percent_order_sum

df_with_revenue15percent = df[(df['cost_of_the_order'] > 5) & (df['cost_of_the_order'] < 20)]
revenue15percent_order_sum = df_with_revenue15percent['cost_of_the_order'].sum()
total_15percentrevenue = 0.15 * revenue15percent_order_sum

total_revenue = total_25percentrevenue + total_15percentrevenue
print("Total revenue of the company", total_revenue)

Total revenue of the company 6166.303

Net Revenue of the complany on all orders is 6133.303 Dollars.

Conclusions:

  • Most of the orders are placed during the Weekend
  • Approximately 25% of the orders are from the top 3 restaurants.
  • Delivery Time During the weekday is high.
  • 784 Customers have ordered only once.
  • Most favoured Cuisine is American(584 orders) and Japanese(470 Orders).

Recommendations and Suggestions:

Delivery

  • Business needs to analyze the demand on the weekends and reduce the delivery time. This will help them to provide better customer experience and improve the ratings.

  • The mean delivery Time for the restaurant with Highest orders Shake Shack is greater than the overall mean delivery time.

The data provided is not sufficient to analyze the patterns of the delivery partners availability. Business should collect more data to locate pattern in demand and supply of food orders and delivery partners

Customers

  • There are 784 customers who have ordered only once. Efforts should be made to analyze that out of 1200 customers why 784 customers have not returned back and ordered.

  • Discount offers could be provided to boost customer ordering on the platform.

  • Feedback offers could be provided to gain insights and data various services offered like total delivery time, restaurant food quality, Cost of the order etc.

Restaurants

  • Since around 25% of the orders are coming from the top 3 restaurant out of 178 restaurants, more analysis is required to understand what are the reasons that the orders are not coming from those restaurants.

  • Some of the reasons orders are coming low could be poor food quality, poor customer service, less food quantity wrt cost of the order.
